&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start Date&lt;/strong&gt;: ASAP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sixteenth, part of Whalar Group, is one of the leading, global, 360° Creator talent management companies. As the home of “good influence,” we’re dedicated to building long-term, strategic partnerships that help Creators fulfill their professional and human potential. We believe in promoting positivity and purpose — enabling Creators to deliver culturally relevant content, achieve deeper audience engagement, and build lasting careers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Andy Warhol once predicted that everyone would have fifteen minutes of fame. We&#39;re here to give creators their Sixteenth minute — and beyond. Learn more about Sixteenth: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.sixteenth.com&quot;&gt;www.sixteenth.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Sixteenth is looking for a Manager / Senior Talent Manager to build, develop, and represent a roster of talent across the Broadcast, Media &amp;amp; PR landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;This role will focus on identifying, signing, and managing individuals whose careers are rooted in television, radio, podcasting, journalism, communications, publicity, cultural commentary, and other public-facing media disciplines. As the lead for this specialist vertical, you will help talent unlock new opportunities, grow their influence, and build long-term, sustainable careers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;You will combine talent discovery, career management, commercial strategy, and relationship-building to support both emerging and established talent. Working closely with Creators, industry partners, and internal stakeholders, you will help shape the next generation of influential voices across media and culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to build a category-defining roster at the intersection of the Creator Economy, traditional media, and cultural influence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Here’s what you’ll do day to day:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, manage, and grow a roster of talent across Broadcast, Media &amp;amp; PR, identifying individuals with strong commercial, cultural, and audience growth potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute long-term career strategies that help talent grow their profile, influence, and opportunities across media, content, speaking engagements, partnerships, and live events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with broadcasters, producers, talent bookers, media organisations, event organisers, and other key industry stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
